<p>In the latest development, wildfires burning across southern Chile for a third day have killed at least 19 people and forced large-scale evacuations, as fast-moving flames hit towns and rural communities. Authorities have declared disaster areas in Ñuble and Biobío, widening emergency powers as crews try to stop the fires spreading further in extreme heat and strong winds. The blazes have destroyed homes and left families without shelter, with reporting from the ground describing neighborhoods reduced to rubble and residents fleeing as conditions shifted quickly.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/9R8VZq0m1OS-iNPNIe8w44kif9IJ0HecogufS0XrY1GsWTlakoOxCds4rFLsw6HBjAMz7moOFSRPqw1vGYxT1sSY1ajmek5PRo5EubJCWbgsufIuhkaAAyszY7FcubStqDomXAyZP324Ffd3DogyD-WSA2MRWeqwfMhkjoWV2V3CBGsFkm9y5XhSsiTo4xPTUWV164O0eodwNA1sYNGfUK614rScD30PHYMuxQG8_w3DDgZvv7E' alt='A woman and two children walk past the remains of a burnt house after a wildfire destroyed hundreds of properties in Punta de Parra, Chile, January 19, 2026.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Massive mobilization: More than 3,500 firefighters have been deployed to battle the blazes, alongside soldiers permitted under the disaster-area declarations.</li><li>Homeless families: Around 1,500 people have been left homeless, with evacuation centers and temporary help becoming urgent priorities.</li><li>Penco devastation: Much of the city of Penco has been destroyed, according to on-the-ground accounts of residents describing how the fire overran homes.</li><li>Weather-driven spread: Reports say extreme heat and strong winds have helped the fires expand rapidly, complicating containment efforts.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Chilean authorities: Officials have treated the situation as a disaster in Ñuble and Biobío, enabling expanded emergency deployment, including soldiers, while firefighters work to contain the blazes. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2026/01/20/chile-wildfires-rage-for-third-day-entire-towns-wiped-out_6749593_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>Residents in affected communities: Some residents describe losing homes as fires swept through populated areas, with Penco among the hardest-hit places cited in first-hand accounts. (<a href='https://www.barrons.com/news/penco-residents-describe-how-chile-wildfires-ravaged-their-homes-2e3ed253'>Barron&#x27;s (AFP)</a>)</li><li>Emergency responders: Firefighters and support forces are focused on suppressing multiple fronts at once amid difficult weather, with evacuations used to protect lives as conditions change. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/chile-fights-wildfires-killed-19-forced-massive-evacuations-129349992'>ABC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/chile-fights-wildfires-killed-19-forced-massive-evacuations-129349992'>Chile fights wildfires that killed 19 and forced massive evacuations</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/trump-nobel-peace-prize-snub-greenland-control-denmark-norway-exchange-13970372.html'>Wildfires rage into third day in southern Chile as death toll continues to rise</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2026/01/20/chile-wildfires-rage-for-third-day-entire-towns-wiped-out_6749593_4.html'>Chile wildfires rage for third day, entire towns wiped out</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.barrons.com/news/penco-residents-describe-how-chile-wildfires-ravaged-their-homes-2e3ed253'>Much of the city of Penco is destroyed as wildfires continue to spread across Chile with the death toll rising to nineteen. (AFP via Barron&#x27;s)</a> - barrons.com</li></ul>